<section id="theme" class="content">
  <div class="row">
    <div class="small-12 columns">
      <h1>Theme</h1>
      <p>“He himself bore our sins in his body on the cross, so that we might die to sins and live for righteousness; by his wounds you have been healed.”<br>I Peter 2:24</p>
      <h2>Seminars</h2>
      <h2><small>Orsolya Horváth</small></h2>
      <p>Ahead, to the Start!
      <br>
      The only source of our faith's birth and renewal is Jesus Christ. Whatever we do, however we behave or try, if our connection with Jesus Christ is distorted, broken or does not even exist, then the whole thing isn't worth a dime. These two seminars hope to help relay the foundations of our connection with Jesus Christ:</p>

      <p>1. Jesus Christ: Person or Paper?
      <br>
      First we shall ask, who is the Redeemer for us today. Can someone who lived about 2000 years ago really be a living person in our everyday lives? To stay in contact with him, do I really always need to read, and always the same thing? What if I get awfully bored of it?</p>

      <p>2. The Joy and Outrage of the Cross
      <br>
      Then we shall ask, what kind of a relationship do I truly have with the Redeemer. Do I really know him? Do I truly follow him? Do I earnestly want him at all?</p>
      
      <h2><small>László Szabó</small></h2>
      <p>With an Analogue Gospel in a Digital World?
      <br>
      The media has radically changed the life of European people. In the battle of free time activities not only have they won over family bonds, traditional cultural elements, but also the churches. Why is intensive media use so appealing, and what does it do to us? Using the latest research results we will take an adventure into the thoughts and values of today's youth, examining the effect of media on them and the current possibilities for mission. Also we will look through the Scriptures for anchors Jesus gives us in his mission statements regarding ministry in a digital world. The seminaries will help us</p>
      <ul>
        <li>consider ministry in a digital world an opportunity rather than a pain,</li>
        <li>undestand ourselves better as we are also impacted by media,</li>
        <li>mediate fundamental christian values in the 21st century more effectively.</li>
      </ul>
      
      <h2><small>Zoltán Szallós-Farkas</small></h2>
      <p>Are you a spiritual person? A spiritual girl or spiritual young man? If your answer wasn't obvious, then I invite you to the first two seminars of my 4-part series. At these presentations we will examine the Biblical definition of spirituality.</p>

      <p>In the continuation we will make clear how the spiritual person deals with sexuality. If you are not sure about your answer, please join us on the 3rd and 4th seminars too.</p>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

