      <h2>László Szabó</h2>
      <span class="th"><%= image_tag '2015/laci.jpg' %></span>
      <p>
        László Szabó is a teacher at the Friedensau Adventist University.
        As a pastor he first did mission work in Tanzania, then later
        worked in Hungary. His main subjects of research are the past, 
        present and future of European mission and the life of the Maasai
        in Tanzania. He currently lives in Germany with his wife, Silvia,
        and their two children (Dominik and Zsanna).
      </p>
    </div>
    <div class="medium-6 columns">
      <h2>Sebastian Matula</h2>
      <span class="th"><%= image_tag '2014/sebastien.jpg' %></span>
      <p>
        Sebastian Matula is currently a second year theology student at
        Newbold College. Was born in Sweden to Hungarian parents and has
        also lived in Hungary for 6 years. Before taking his faith
        seriously and entering ministry, he was a professional football
        player with a bright future. But an injury stopped him, which
        eventually led him to reconsider the importance of life and
